<recipe>
<title>
Cannoli Muffins
</title>
<details>
SERVINGS: 12
</details>
<ingredients>
1 c Â½ . all-purpose flour
1 tsp . baking powder
1/2 tsp . salt
1/4 tsp . baking soda
1/4 c . olive oil
1/2 c . dark brown sugar packed
1/4 c . granulated sugar
1 large egg
3/4 c . part-skim ricotta
1/2 c . low-fat milk
1-2 T . frozen orange juice concentrate depending on how strong you want the orange flavor to be
1 tsp . vanilla extract
1/2 c . dark chocolate chips
1/4 c . semisweet mini chocolate chips
1/4 c . chopped pistachios
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
In a medium sized bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, and baking soda, Set aside.
In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil and sugars.
Add egg, and whisk until well-combined.
Add the ricotta, milk, orange juice, and vanilla; mix well. If you'd like a subtle orange juice flavor, add 1 tablespoon. If you want a more pronounced orange flavor, add 2 tablespoons.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet, and mix lightly, just until incorporated.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Scoop the batter into the muffin tins.
Sprinkle with mini chocolate chips and chopped pistachios.
Bake until the muffins are puffed and golden and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 15-20 minutes.
Let cool in pan for about 5 minutes. Then remove from pan and cool on a rack.
</instructions>
</recipe>
